    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Tarantula Octapeptide-1 is a single chain peptide containing 8 amino acids consisting of arginine, cysteine, glycine, lysine, serine and tryptophan. It is synthetically produced based on a sequence from U1-theraphotoxin-Lsp1c which is found in the tarantula, Lasiodora sp. The parent protein contains a maximum of 99 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
